# Build-context excludes for the poetics workbench image (Dockerfile.poetics).
#
# deploy/ is intentionally NOT excluded: it holds the baked database snapshot
# (deploy/evaluations.db) that the image reads via EVAL_DB_PATH. Everything
# excluded below is either rebuilt in the container (node_modules) or not read
# by the poetics browser at runtime.

# Rebuilt inside the container by `npm install`. Must be excluded so the host's
# macOS-native better-sqlite3 binary never overwrites the alpine one.
node_modules

# Version control + CI
.git
.github
.gitignore

# Local databases + the data/ symlink (the real DB is baked via deploy/).
data

# Large trees the poetics browser does not need to serve:
#  - logs/exports: disk-backed transcript + replay artifacts (see DEPLOYMENT.md;
#    full-transcript drill-downs are degraded in this image by design)
#  - docs: the paper PDFs; the paper is linked from the public arc page instead
#  - config/poetics-calibration: 68 MB of calibration runs, only an example path
logs
exports
docs
artifacts
config/poetics-calibration

# Test + tooling noise
tests
coverage
tmp
*.log
npm-debug.log*

# Secrets + OS noise — never bake these into an image
.env
.env.*
.DS_Store
